properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued January 9 at 9:16PM CST until January 12 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...HEAVY SNOW POSSIBLE IN NORTHEAST AND EAST CENTRAL WISCONSIN
LATE SATURDAY AFTERNOON AND SATURDAY NIGHT...

.A winter storm moving from Illinois to Lower Michigan could bring
heavy snow to northeast and east central Wisconsin late Saturday
afternoon and Saturday night. Snowfall amounts of 6 to 12 inches
are possible. Strong north to northeast winds will result in
blowing snow. There will also be increased potential for ice
shoves, lakeshore flooding, and shoreline erosion.

* WHAT...Heavy snow possible. Total snow accumulations of 6 to
12 inches possible. Winds could gust as high as 40 mph,
causing considerable blowing and drifting snow.

* WHERE...Portions of central, east central and northeast
Wisconsin.

* WHEN...From Saturday afternoon through late Saturday night.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult to impossible. Areas
of blowing snow could significantly reduce visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong north to northeast winds will
increase the potential for ice shoves, lakeshore and bayshore
flooding, and shoreline erosion.
properties.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH LATE SATURDAY NIGHT
